Place the files in following folders

Files:
Make sure your files are organized like this in your src/main/java/com/soc/siem folder:
SiemBackendApplication.java (The "Brain")

model/LogEntry.java (The Data Structure)
repository/LogRepository.java (The Database Link)
service/SyslogListener.java (The UDP "Ear")
controller/SocController.java (The Web API)

Place the index file:
src/main/resources/static/index.html

Run:
Start the Java App: Stop the current process (Ctrl+C).
Run: mvn spring-boot:run (or click the Play button in VSCODE).
Open the Browser: Go to http://localhost:8080/.


Testing:
Send an "Attack": Open your PowerShell window and send a log that contains the word "attack":
PowerShell
$u = New-Object System.Net.Sockets.UdpClient; $u.Connect("127.0.0.1", 10514)
$p = [System.Text.Encoding]::ASCII.GetBytes("SECURITY ALERT: SQL Injection attack detected on login form")
$u.Send($p, $p.Length); $u.Close()
